pidgin-guifications
------------------------------------------
Guifications is a Pidgin plugin that displays 'toaster' popups in a 
user-defined corner of the screen, similar to features that have been 
added to the official MSN Messenger (now called Windows Live Messenger), 
Yahoo! Messenger and AOL Instant Messenger clients. It's highly 
configurable, easy to use, and has theme support. It really is the 
end-all, be-all toaster pop-up plugin for Pidgin!

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.7.0-62
  libgcc1-4.3.4-1
  libgdk_pixbuf2.0_0-2.16.6-1
  libglib2.0_0-2.20.5-1
  libgtk2.0_0-2.16.6-1
  libintl8-0.17-11
  libpango1.0_0-1.24.5-1
  libpurple0-2.6.2-1
  libX11_6-1.2.2-1
  pidgin-2.6.2-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf2.5-2.63-10
  automake1.9-1.9.6-10
  binutils-2.19.51-1
  cygport-0.9.9-1
  gawk-3.1.7-1
  gcc4-core-4.3.4-1
  gettext-devel-0.17-11
  gnome-common-2.26.0-2
  intltool-0.40.6-1
  libtool-2.2.7a-14
  make-3.81-2
  pkg-config-0.23b-10
  sed-4.1.5-2

Canonical website:
  http://plugins.guifications.org/trac/wiki/Guifications

Canonical download:
  http://downloads.guifications.org/plugins/Guifications2/

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  unpack pidgin-guifications-2.16-X-src.tar.bz2
    if you use setup to install this src package, it will be
	 unpacked under /usr/src automatically
  cd /usr/src
  cygport ./pidgin-guifications-2.16-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/pidgin-guifications-2.16-X-src.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/pidgin-guifications-2.16-X.tar.bz2

-------------------------------------------

